You have &quot;buka&quot; for both open and unlock. And the &quot;can't XXXX&quot; message is the same for both as well, which made things a bit confusing at first. It's running the unlock code instead of open when you type something like &quot;buka kulkas&quot;, and your &quot;kulkas&quot; is not unlockable. <!-- s:) --><img src="{SMILIES_PATH}/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><!-- s:) -->

Another note: if you provide a GetDefaultPrefix function in your Indonesia file, then you can get rid of the English.aslx include. It would be something like:
[code:3dkfz44w]  &lt;function name=&quot;GetDefaultPrefix&quot; type=&quot;string&quot; parameters=&quot;obj&quot;&gt;
    return (&quot;some prefix based on the object&quot;)
  &lt;/function&gt;[/code:3dkfz44w]
